parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Upper and Lower Ball Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper and lower ball joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and can also result in the wheel falling off, which can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a clicking or knocking noise
the steering becomes hard to control
the vehicle shakes while making turns
and the ball joints rattle and clunk.
